description: View larger The smartphone reinvented around you Tailored to you. .. The Nokia Lumia 635 has almost everything you've been looking for in a smartphone packed into a beautifully designed silhouette. With its powerful quad-core processor and Windows operating system, the Lumia 635 keeps up with your day-to-day activities. Features of the Nokia Lumia 635 include: - Windows Phone 8.1 - add a personalized touch to your experience. - Action Center – Get notifications from apps, texts, see your missed calls, and more. - Word Flow – Socially interact and text on the intuitive keyboard. - Cortana - Your virtual personal assistant learns about you and offers helpful suggestions. View larger View larger View larger View larger A personalized experience Windows Phone 8.1 allows you to customize your own experience. With the Start Background feature you can personalize your start screen by adding a picture behind the Live Tiles. Add apps to your Live Tiles, resize them, and change their color to suit your taste. Microsoft Office is also built into your phone and can easily be synced with your Windows laptop or tablet. Your own personal assistant Powered by Bing, Cortana gives recommendations and suggestions tailored to you. By learning about you, she anticipates your needs, whether it be a weather update, driving directions, or a reminder to call back your friend. Stay informed Get access to notifications from your favorite apps, texts, emails, missed calls, and more with just one swipe from the top of the phone. Tapping on any of these notifications will launch that app or feature. You can also customize your quick settings from the Action Center. A new way to type Chat, text, and connect with the Word Flow keyboard. Its intuitive design allows you to swipe through letters for a quick typing experience.

description: Nokia Lumia 530, is an entry-level smartphone running on Microsoft Windows Phone 8.1. It features a 4.0-inch multi-touch display with a resolution of 480 x 854 pixels, resulting a pixel density of 245 ppi. The chip inside is Qualcomm Snapdragon 200 with quad-core 1.2 GHz CPU and Adreno 302 GPU. System memory is 512 MB RAM, while internal storage is only 4 GB. That’s very limited storage capacity, but you can have more storage with a microSD card up to 128 GB. A camera with 1/4” sensor size can capture images up to 5 MP. For video capture, the camera supports up to 480p @ 30fps. It doesn’t have secondary camera. For internet access via mobile network, it supports HSPA+ 21 Mbps and HSUPA 5.76 Mbps. Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n allows you to connect to wireless router around you. This Lumia smartphone can be used as a portable hotspot too. Bluetooth 4.0 makes transferring files easy. Equipped with Lithium-Ion 1430 mAh battery, it provides up to 528 hours of stand-by time and up to 51 hours for playing music. Lumia 530 has some color options including dark grey, bright green, bright orange, and white. description: The Nokia Lumia 1320 - Make an impact! Continuing to redefine smartphone innovation, Nokia introduce the Lumia 1320. With a 6" display and the latest software advancements for Windows Phone, the Lumia 1320 is perfectly suited for both productivity and entertainment. Thanks to the increased screen size, a new third column of tiles on the home screen means people can see and do more. Bringing larger displays to the award-winning Lumia design, the new format is coupled with some of the most advanced camera innovations so people can capture and share the world around them. With A 720p HD display, 4G LTE connectivity and a smart design available in a range of colours, Nokia have designed the Lumia 1320 to be far more than just a smartphone. Get more out of your videos, games and apps with the big screen, and turn your moments into great stories with Nokia Camera, Nokia Storyteller and exclusive photo editing tools like Cinemagraph and Creative Studio. The Lumia 1320 will soon become an extension of your busy life. Pre-loaded Nokia Camera lets you capture great photos, and you can use the Smart mode to create a sequence of motion, add motion blur effects and more. Or create some magic with innovative photo editing tools like Creative Studio and Cinemagraph. Moving your apps, tunes and photos from your old phone is easy. The free Nokia app lets you seamlessly transition to your new Nokia Lumia. The pre-installed 'Transfer My Data' app on the Lumia range of phones moves all your contacts over using Bluetooth. Welcome Home to Windows Phone lets you move all your media and contacts in one go. With OneDrive, your photos, videos, notes and office docs are available to you wherever you are. A whopping 7Gb of free storage space and automatic sync means you'll never have to worry about losing your stuff.

description: Meet the Galaxy S8 - Infinitely Brilliant. The Galaxy S8 has the world's first Infinity Screen, A screen without limits. The expansive display stretches from edge to edge, giving you the most amount of screen in the least amount of space. The revolutionary design of the Galaxy S8 begins from the inside out. We rethought every part of the phone's layout to break through the confines of the smartphone screen. So all you see is pure content and no bezel. It's the biggest, most immersive screen on a Galaxy smartphone of this size. And it's easy to hold in one hand. The Infinity Display has an incredible end-to-end screen that spills over the phone’s sides, forming a completely smooth, continuous surface with no bumps or angles. It’s pure, pristine, uninterrupted glass. And it takes up the entire front of the phone, flowing seamlessly into the aluminum shell. The result is a beautifully curved, perfectly symmetrical, singular object. Capture life as it happens with the Galaxy S8 cameras. The 12MP rear camera and the 8MP front camera are so accurate and fast that you won't miss a moment, day or night. Prying eyes are not a problem when you have iris scanning on the Galaxy S8. No two irises have the same pattern, not even yours, and they're nearly impossible to replicate. That means with iris scanning, your phone and its contents open to your eyes only. And when you need to unlock really fast, face recognition is a handy option. You never really stop using your phone. That's why Galaxy S8 is driven by the world's first 10nm processor. It's fast and powerful and increases battery efficiency. Plus, there's the ability to expand storage, and to work through rain and dust with IP68-rated performance.

about: ['DOES THIS DEVICE NEED A SIM CARD: Yes it does Being that this device is GSM unlocked it will work on any GSM Network with a NANO size SIM Card (and the NANO Sim card is NOT enclosed) you will need to contact your Network Provider to acquire your complimentary Sim card (Free from most Carriers with activation of an account)', 'WHAT NETWORK FREQUENCIES ARE SUPPORTED BY THIS DEVICE: GSM: GSM850, GSM900, DCS1800, PCS1900 UMTS: B2(1900), B4(AWS), B5(850) 4G LTE: B2(1900) ,B4(AWS), B5(850), B12(700)', 'HOW LONG CAN I EXPECT THE BATTERY TO LAST ME: Well the battery (EB-BG530BBU) has 2600mAh which in a Usage time frame means Battery Talk Time Up to 9 hours Music Play Time of up to 71 hrs Video Play Time up to 13 hrs Internet Use Time on 3G up to 11 hrs on LTE: up to 12 hrs on Wi-Fi: up to 13 hrs before you need to recharge the battery.', "WHAT DOES UNLOCKED REALLY MEAN: Unlocked devices are compatible with GSM carriers the kinds that Use SIM Cards for Service like AT&T and T-Mobile as well as with GSM SIM cards (e.g. H20, Straight Talk, and select prepaid carriers) Unlocked Devices will not work with CDMA Carriers the kinds that don't use sim cards for service like Sprint, Verizon, Boost or Virgin (contact your network provider prior to purchasing for verification that they support GSM frequencies)."]
